quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  77,1,By those sent forth one after another
  77,2,That blow violently in tempestuous gusts
  77,3,And scatter far and wide
  77,4,"Then separate them, one from another"
  77,5,Then spread abroad a message
  77,6,Whether of justification or of warning
  77,7,Surely what you are promised must come to pass
  77,8,Then when the stars become dim
  77,9,When the heaven is cleft asunder
  77,10,When the mountains are scattered as dust
  77,11,And when the messengers are all appointed a time
  77,12,For what day are these deferred
  77,13,For the day of sorting out
  77,14,And what will explain to you what the day of sorting out is
  77,15,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,16,Did We not destroy people in the past
  77,17,So We will make those of late follow them
  77,18,This is how We deal with the people of sin
  77,19,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,20,Have We not created you from a fluid seemingly worthless
  77,21,"Which We placed in a place of rest, firmly fixed"
  77,22,For a period determined
  77,23,"And We decide, for We are the best to decide"
  77,24,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,25,Have We not made the earth to draw together–
  77,26,The living and the dead
  77,27,"And made therein mountains standing firm and lofty, and provided for you sweet water"
  77,28,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,29,It will be said “Go to that which you used to reject as false
  77,30,“Depart to a shadow in three columns
  77,31,"“Which yields no shade of coolness, and is of no use against the fierce blaze.”"
  77,32,“Indeed it throws about sparks as forts
  77,33,“As if there were yellow camels.”
  77,34,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,35,That will be a day when they will be unable to speak
  77,36,Nor will it be open to them to put forth pleas
  77,37,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth
  77,38,That will be a day of sorting out. We will gather you together with those before you
  77,39,"Now, if you have a plot, use it against Me"
  77,40,Ah woe that day to the rejecters of truth